The Tommy G. Robertson Railroad is a heritage railway at Six Flags St. Louis in Eureka, Missouri. It opened with the park on June 5, 1971,  when it was then known as the "Six Flags Railroad".


== History ==
The Tommy G. Robertson Railroad opened on June 5, 1971 as the "Six Flags Railroad". Years later, it was renamed the "Tommy G. Robertson Railroad".


